OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773821068
OL,3,CShould the UK cancel or delay King's
OL,4,Cstate visit to the White House?
OL,6,FHe has referred to Starmer as "no
OL,7,FWinston Churchill", criticised him for
OL,8,Fsending warships when the war is
OL,9,F"already won" and that the UK
OL,10,Freluctance to join his war was
OL,11,F"terrible".
OL,13,FAt the White House this week, Mr Trump
OL,14,Ftold reporters: "I was not happy with
OL,15,Fthe UK. I think they'll be involved,
OL,16,Fmaybe, but they should be involved
OL,17,Fenthusiastically."
OL,19,FPreviously, senior British diplomatic
OL,20,Fsources told ITV News that the royal
OL,21,Fvisit would still go ahead.
