OL,3,CShould the UK cancel or delay King's
OL,4,Cstate visit to the White House?
OL,6,FThey explained the trip is to
OL,7,Fcelebrate the 250th anniversary of US
OL,8,Findependence, and it was therefore
OL,9,Fabout the people of the United States,
OL,10,Fnot about one particular occupant of
OL,11,Fthe Oval Office.
OL,13,FBut as Mr Trump continues to publicly
OL,14,Fcriticise the British Prime Minister,
OL,15,Fa delay to the visit may become
OL,16,Finevitable in order to reduce any risk
OL,17,Fof drawing the King and Queen into a
OL,18,Flive and divisive political issue.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
